Preparation

  • Install the   tidyverse
  • Load it with   library(tidyverse)

The grammar of graphics

ggplot   is based on the   grammar of graphics :

  A statistical graphic is a   mapping   of   data   variables to   aesthetic   attributes of   geometric objects.


These ingredients appear in   ggplot   as   data ,   aes , and   geom   — examples will clarify things.

2007 Gapminder data

  • Geom : point
  • GDP : x-coordinate aesthetic
  • Life expectancy : y-coordinate aesthetic
  • Population : size aesthetic
  • Continent : color aesthetic

Scatterplots

ggplot( data = ICUAdmissions, mapping = aes(x=HeartRate, y=Systolic)) + geom_point()

Scatterplots

ggplot( ICUAdmissions, aes(HeartRate, Systolic)) + geom_point()

Scatterplots

ggplot( data = ICUAdmissions, mapping = aes(x=HeartRate, y=Systolic, color=Sex)) + geom_point()

Line graphs

ggplot( Hurricanes, aes(Year, Hurricanes)) + geom_line()

Histograms

ggplot(ICUAdmissions, aes(HeartRate)) + geom_histogram()

Histograms

ggplot(ICUAdmissions, aes(HeartRate)) + geom_histogram( binwidth=5 )

Histograms

ggplot(ICUAdmissions, aes(HeartRate)) + geom_histogram() + facet_wrap(~Sex)

Boxplots

ggplot(ICUAdmissions, aes(x=Sex,y=Systolic)) + geom_boxplot()

Boxplots

ggplot(ICUAdmissions, aes(x=Sex,y=Systolic)) + geom_boxplot() + coord_flip()

Boxplots

ggplot(Hurricanes, aes(x="",y=Hurricanes)) + geom_boxplot()

Barplots

ggplot(StudentSurvey,aes(Award)) + geom_bar()

Barplots

ggplot(StudentSurvey,aes(Award,fill=Gender)) + geom_bar()

Barplots

ggplot(StudentSurvey,aes(Award,fill=Gender)) + geom_bar( position="dodge" )

Barplots

ggplot(StudentSurvey,aes(Award)) + geom_bar() + facet_wrap(~Gender)
